    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

    <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> July 2025</p>

    <p>At XBTCR, we are committed to protecting your privacy and safeguarding your personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect any data we may receive from you when you interact with our website or services.</p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Personal Information:</strong> We do not collect any personally identifiable information unless voluntarily submitted by users through contact forms or email.</li>
      <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> We may use analytics tools to track website traffic and performance. These tools do not store personal user data.</li>
      <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> Our website may use cookies to enhance your user experience. You can disable cookies through your browser settings.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
    <p>Any data we collect is used solely to improve the website, respond to user inquiries, and manage project-related communication. We do not sell or share your data with third parties.</p>

    <h2>3. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>We may use trusted third-party services such as GitHub Pages or email providers. These services have their own privacy policies which you are encouraged to review.</p>

    <h2>4. Data Security</h2>
    <p>We take reasonable precautions to protect any data submitted to us. However, no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure.</p>

    <h2>5. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>This Privacy Policy may be updated at any time. All changes will be posted on this page, and your continued use of the website implies acceptance of those changes.</p>

    <h2>6. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, you can reach out via our <a href="contact.html">Contact page</a> or Telegram group: <a href="https://t.me/xbtcr_bsc" target="_blank">t.me/xbtcr_bsc</a>.</p>
